---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Aetna International in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'Spanish Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'spain-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'us-expat-advantage', text: 'US Expat Advantage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-in-spain', text: 'Using Your Insurance in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Aetna in Spain', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs GeoBlue', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'spainPrice', header: 'Spain (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', spainPrice: '$150-200/mo', visaCompliant: 'Check requirements' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Prime', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', spainPrice: '$200-280/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Platinum', coverage: 'Comprehensive', spainPrice: '$280-380/mo', visaCompliant: true },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'spanish', header: 'Spanish Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', aetna: '$200-280', spanish: '€60-120' },
  { factor: 'US Coverage', aetna: 'Full integrated', spanish: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Spain', aetna: 'Worldwide', spanish: 'Limited/None' },
  { factor: 'Network in Spain', aetna: 'Good (major cities)', spanish: 'Extensive' },
  { factor: 'English Support', aetna: 'Full 24/7', spanish: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Portability if You Move', aetna: 'Fully portable', spanish: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Best For', aetna: 'US expats', spanish: 'Long-term Spain residents' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Health Insurance in Spain"
  description="Guide to using Aetna International in Spain. Ideal for US expats needing seamless US and Spain coverage. Visa compliance, network, and pricing."
  headline="Aetna International Health Insurance in Spain"
  subheadline="The top choice for US expats in Spain who need integrated coverage in both countries. Here's what you need to know."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/spain-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Spain Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Aetna International in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International is the premier choice for American expats in Spain. As part of CVS Health, Aetna offers something most international insurers can't match: seamless integration with the US healthcare system.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're a US citizen living in Spain who visits family back home, needs ongoing care from US specialists, or might eventually repatriate, Aetna International eliminates the coverage gap that would otherwise exist.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.7M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers (incl. US)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">190+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">24/7</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Multilingual support</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Spain-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Aetna International costs for US expats in Spain."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">Spanish Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International plans are accepted for Spanish visa applications. However, because Aetna is US-based rather than EU-regulated, some consulates may require additional documentation.
  </p>

  <h3>Visa Types Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Non-Lucrative Visa</strong> — Popular with US retirees in Spain</li>
    <li><strong>Digital Nomad Visa</strong> — For remote workers</li>
    <li><strong>Student Visa</strong> — For US students studying in Spain</li>
    <li><strong>Golden Visa</strong> — Investment-based residency</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Documentation for Visa Applications</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of coverage (can be translated to Spanish)</li>
    <li>Confirmation of coverage scope and dates</li>
    <li>Letter confirming no copays (Prime/Platinum plans)</li>
    <li>Policy documentation in English</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Visa Tip for US Expats</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Some Spanish consulates prefer EU-regulated insurers. If you encounter resistance, Aetna can provide additional documentation. Alternatively, consider <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/allianz-care" class="underline">Allianz Care</a> or <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/axa-global" class="underline">AXA Global</a> for visa purposes, then switch to Aetna once your visa is approved.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="spain-network">Network Coverage in Spain</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International maintains a network of providers in Spain's major cities. While smaller than some EU-based insurers' Spanish networks, coverage is solid in expat-heavy areas.
  </p>

  <h3>Network by City</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Madrid:</strong> Multiple hospital options with direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>Barcelona:</strong> Good coverage in city center and suburbs</li>
    <li><strong>Valencia:</strong> Major hospitals available</li>
    <li><strong>Costa del Sol:</strong> Coverage in Málaga, Marbella area</li>
    <li><strong>Seville:</strong> Regional hospital access</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Out-of-Network Care</h3>
  <p>
    You can see any licensed provider in Spain. For non-network providers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pay upfront and submit for reimbursement</li>
    <li>Reimbursement typically within 5-10 business days</li>
    <li>Spanish receipts (facturas) accepted</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna offers Pioneer series plans for individual expats. Pricing includes US coverage—a key differentiator.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices include worldwide coverage with full US access. Higher than some competitors because US coverage is integrated, not an add-on.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Navigator Plans (Modular Option)</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna's Navigator plans let you customize coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Core hospital coverage (required)</li>
    <li>Outpatient module (add if needed)</li>
    <li>Dental module</li>
    <li>Vision module</li>
    <li>Maternity module</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Navigator can be more cost-effective if you don't need all benefits included in Pioneer tiers.
  </p>

  <h2 id="us-expat-advantage">US Expat Advantage</h2>
  <p>
    The primary reason to choose Aetna International in Spain is the US coverage integration:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">What You Get</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>Full Aetna US network access</li>
        <li>Direct billing at US hospitals</li>
        <li>Aetna's negotiated US rates</li>
        <li>No separate US coverage add-on</li>
        <li>Seamless care during US visits</li>
        <li>Continuity if you repatriate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why It Matters</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Visiting family? You're covered</li>
        <li>US specialist needed? Direct access</li>
        <li>Moving back? No gap in coverage</li>
        <li>US prescriptions? Portable coverage</li>
        <li>No 40-60% premium increase for US</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Comparison: Aetna vs Other Insurers for US Coverage</h3>
  <p>
    With Cigna Global or Allianz Care, adding US coverage increases premiums by 40-60%. Aetna's US coverage is integrated, often making the total cost similar or lower for US expats who need both.
  </p>

  <h2 id="claims-in-spain">Using Your Insurance in Spain</h2>

  <h3>Direct Billing</h3>
  <p>
    At network hospitals in Spain, show your Aetna card for direct billing. You pay only your deductible or copay. Contact Aetna in advance for pre-authorization on planned procedures.
  </p>

  <h3>Reimbursement Claims</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
    <li>Pay the Spanish provider directly</li>
    <li>Get itemized receipt (factura)</li>
    <li>Submit via Aetna app or online portal</li>
    <li>Receive reimbursement in 5-10 business days</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>When in the US</h3>
  <p>
    Use your Aetna card at any Aetna network provider in the US—same as a domestic Aetna member. Direct billing, negotiated rates, full coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Aetna in Spain</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>US citizens living in Spain</li>
        <li>Expats who visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>Those with US doctors/specialists</li>
        <li>People who may repatriate</li>
        <li>US company employees abroad</li>
        <li>Families with US healthcare needs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Non-US expats (Aetna is US-focused)</li>
        <li>Those who never visit the US</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious without US needs</li>
        <li>Those wanting EU-regulated insurer</li>
        <li>Long-term Spain residents</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Best for US Expats"
    description="If you're American in Spain, Aetna's integrated US coverage is hard to beat."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Aetna International the same as regular Aetna?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International is the global division of Aetna (CVS Health). Your card works at US Aetna providers, but the plan is designed for people living outside the US.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I keep my US doctors while living in Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. During US visits, you can see your regular Aetna network doctors. For ongoing US prescriptions, coordinate with Aetna—some can be filled internationally or during visits.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I'm not a US citizen?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International is available to non-US citizens, but the US coverage advantage is less relevant. Non-Americans in Spain may find better value with <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/allianz-care">Allianz Care</a> or <a href="/countries/spain/insurance/axa-global">AXA Global</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>Does Aetna cover Spanish public hospitals?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna covers private healthcare in Spain. Emergency care at public hospitals may be covered and reimbursed, but routine care should be at private providers.
  </p>

  <h3>How does Aetna compare to GeoBlue for Spain?</h3>
  <p>
    Both are excellent for US expats. Aetna offers modular Navigator plans for more customization; GeoBlue offers the Blue Cross network. Coverage and pricing are similar. <a href="/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue">See our full comparison</a>.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Spain and the US?"
    description="Get a personalized Aetna International quote for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Network availability, pricing, and visa requirements change. Verify all information with Aetna International and Spanish authorities before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
